ANC chief whip Jackson Mthembu has reportedly lashed out at President Jacob Zuma accusing him of using state resources to fight Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan.He also called on all ANC executive leadership to step down. Mthembu reportedly told City Press newspaper that the governing party with its current leadership is worse than its apartheid predecessors.Talking about Zuma, sources reveal that Mthembu likened him to Hitler and said that he is even worse. He just says stuff that I don t think Hitler would say and I mean it, said Mthembu. He and Hitler would be good friends I think. Have tea together or something. Just look at the things he says! Terribly mean stuff if you ask me concluded Mthembu.Image by: Freddy Mavunda/Financial Mail